@JesseKGreen Hurray for a writer’s toolkit . . . waiting for the Muses to speak is such an unreliable way to meet a deadline.

I bet you, like me, enjoyed Bill Murray’s instruction to his staff writer in The French Dispatch:

“Just try to make it sound like you wrote it that way on purpose.”

